  "elapsed_s": 3.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "You should take the [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] help, you know, the service people-- the servants, and-- and help distribute foods and clothes and wood, and mainly a lot of food.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My understanding is that the [GERMAN], [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] the title was-- they were-- they were from Vienna.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they-- her father, my grandmother's father, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] he was a professor.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he wrote a-- some special type of [PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS] books.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And they always used to say how wonderful it was, you know, when-- because there was an expression that the Germans and the Austrians used to use.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Maybe in those days they used to say, 'Leben und leben lassen.' Live and let live.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But this really was not-- I did not experience that.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I experienced just the opposite.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I'm sorry, right.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I don't know exactly.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We had very little to do with the non-Jewish people.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we really didn't have any neighbors that would live next door.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So all I know, that we know that-- we knew that the antisemitism was always present, especially on Easter time.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We used to close the gate and put the [NON-ENGLISH] on the door, close the-- because they would throw stones.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And Christmas was probably the worst time because they-- the Pollacks truly believed that the Jews killed Christ, they-- that the Jews killed their God.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And the antisemitism in Poland was inbred in-- at-- in home already.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "When the chil-- they talked about it, about the dirty Jews at home before the children even started school.",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
